            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/19c8aa1ed0195415/toc/np-199",
            "caption": "CHAPTER XVII. OF THE CAUSES, GENERATION, AND DEFINITION OF A COMMON-WEALTH",
            "tags": "$:/plugins/twpub/19c8aa1ed0195415/toc",
            "target": "$:/plugins/twpub/19c8aa1ed0195415/text/000001268",
            "list": "        ",
            "role": "toc"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/19c8aa1ed0195415/toc/np-210": {
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/19c8aa1ed0195415/toc/np-210",
            "caption": "The Act Of Instituting A Common-wealth, What",
            "tags": "$:/plugins/twpub/19c8aa1ed0195415/toc/np-209",
            "target": "$:/plugins/twpub/19c8aa1ed0195415/text/000001326",
            "list": "",
            "role": "toc"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/19c8aa1ed0195415/toc/np-211": {
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/19c8aa1ed0195415/toc/np-211",
            "caption": "The Consequences To Such Institution, Are 1. The Subjects Cannot Change The Forme Of Government",
            "tags": "$:/plugins/twpub/19c8aa1ed0195415/toc/np-209",
            "target": "$:/plugins/twpub/19c8aa1ed0195415/text/000001330",
            "list": "",
            "role": "toc"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/19c8aa1ed0195415/toc/np-212": {
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/19c8aa1ed0195415/toc/np-212",
            "caption": "2. Soveraigne Power Cannot Be Forfeited",
            "tags": "$:/plugins/twpub/19c8aa1ed0195415/toc/np-209",
            "target": "$:/plugins/twpub/19c8aa1ed0195415/text/000001338",
            "list": "",
            "role": "toc"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/19c8aa1ed0195415/toc/np-213": {
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/19c8aa1ed0195415/toc/np-213",
            "caption": "3. No Man Can Without Injustice Protest Against The Institution Of The Soveraigne Declared By The Major Part.",
            "tags": "$:/plugins/twpub/19c8aa1ed0195415/toc/np-209",
            "target": "$:/plugins/twpub/19c8aa1ed0195415/text/000001342",
            "list": "",
            "role": "toc"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/19c8aa1ed0195415/toc/np-214": {
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/19c8aa1ed0195415/toc/np-214",
            "caption": "4. The Soveraigns Actions Cannot Be Justly Accused By The Subject",
            "tags": "$:/plugins/twpub/19c8aa1ed0195415/toc/np-209",
            "target": "$:/plugins/twpub/19c8aa1ed0195415/text/000001346",
            "list": "",
            "role": "toc"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/19c8aa1ed0195415/toc/np-215": {
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/19c8aa1ed0195415/toc/np-215",
            "caption": "5. What Soever The Soveraigne Doth, Is Unpunishable By The Subject",
            "tags": "$:/plugins/twpub/19c8aa1ed0195415/toc/np-209",
            "target": "$:/plugins/twpub/19c8aa1ed0195415/text/000001350",
            "list": "",
            "role": "toc"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/19c8aa1ed0195415/toc/np-216": {
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/19c8aa1ed0195415/toc/np-216",
            "caption": "6. The Soveraigne Is Judge Of What Is Necessary For The Peace And Defence Of His Subjects",
            "tags": "$:/plugins/twpub/19c8aa1ed0195415/toc/np-209",
            "target": "$:/plugins/twpub/19c8aa1ed0195415/text/000001354",
            "list": "",
            "role": "toc"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/19c8aa1ed0195415/toc/np-217": {
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/19c8aa1ed0195415/toc/np-217",
            "caption": "And Judge Of What Doctrines Are Fit To Be Taught Them",
            "tags": "$:/plugins/twpub/19c8aa1ed0195415/toc/np-209",
            "target": "$:/plugins/twpub/19c8aa1ed0195415/text/000001358",
            "list": "",
            "role": "toc"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/19c8aa1ed0195415/toc/np-218": {
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/19c8aa1ed0195415/toc/np-218",
            "caption": "7. The Right of making Rules, whereby the Subject may every man know what is so his owne, as no other Subject can without injustice take it from him",
            "tags": "$:/plugins/twpub/19c8aa1ed0195415/toc/np-209",
            "target": "$:/plugins/twpub/19c8aa1ed0195415/text/000001362",
            "list": "",
            "role": "toc"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/19c8aa1ed0195415/toc/np-219": {
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/19c8aa1ed0195415/toc/np-219",
            "caption": "8. To Him Also Belongeth The Right Of All Judicature And Decision Of Controversies:",
            "tags": "$:/plugins/twpub/19c8aa1ed0195415/toc/np-209",
            "target": "$:/plugins/twpub/19c8aa1ed0195415/text/000001366",
            "list": "",
            "role": "toc"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/19c8aa1ed0195415/toc/np-220": {
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/19c8aa1ed0195415/toc/np-220",
            "caption": "9. And Of Making War, And Peace, As He Shall Think Best:",
            "tags": "$:/plugins/twpub/19c8aa1ed0195415/toc/np-209",
            "target": "$:/plugins/twpub/19c8aa1ed0195415/text/000001370",
            "list": "",
            "role": "toc"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/19c8aa1ed0195415/toc/np-221": {
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/19c8aa1ed0195415/toc/np-221",
            "caption": "10. And Of Choosing All Counsellours, And Ministers, Both Of Peace, And Warre:",
            "tags": "$:/plugins/twpub/19c8aa1ed0195415/toc/np-209",
            "target": "$:/plugins/twpub/19c8aa1ed0195415/text/000001374",
            "list": "",
            "role": "toc"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/19c8aa1ed0195415/toc/np-222": {
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/19c8aa1ed0195415/toc/np-222",
            "caption": "11. And Of Rewarding, And Punishing, And That (Where No Former Law hath Determined The Measure Of It) Arbitrary:",
            "tags": "$:/plugins/twpub/19c8aa1ed0195415/toc/np-209",
            "target": "$:/plugins/twpub/19c8aa1ed0195415/text/000001378",
            "list": "",
            "role": "toc"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/19c8aa1ed0195415/toc/np-223": {
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/19c8aa1ed0195415/toc/np-223",
            "caption": "12. And Of Honour And Order",
            "tags": "$:/plugins/twpub/19c8aa1ed0195415/toc/np-209",
            "target": "$:/plugins/twpub/19c8aa1ed0195415/text/000001382",
            "list": "",
            "role": "toc"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/19c8aa1ed0195415/toc/np-224": {
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/19c8aa1ed0195415/toc/np-224",
            "caption": "These Rights Are Indivisible",
            "tags": "$:/plugins/twpub/19c8aa1ed0195415/toc/np-209",
            "target": "$:/plugins/twpub/19c8aa1ed0195415/text/000001386",
            "list": "",
            "role": "toc"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/19c8aa1ed0195415/toc/np-225": {
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/19c8aa1ed0195415/toc/np-225",
            "caption": "And Can By No Grant Passe Away Without Direct Renouncing Of The Soveraign Power",
            "tags": "$:/plugins/twpub/19c8aa1ed0195415/toc/np-209",
            "target": "$:/plugins/twpub/19c8aa1ed0195415/text/000001390",
            "list": "",
            "role": "toc"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/19c8aa1ed0195415/toc/np-226": {
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/19c8aa1ed0195415/toc/np-226",
            "caption": "The Power And Honour Of Subjects Vanisheth In The Presence Of The Power Soveraign",
            "tags": "$:/plugins/twpub/19c8aa1ed0195415/toc/np-209",
            "target": "$:/plugins/twpub/19c8aa1ed0195415/text/000001394",
            "list": "",
            "role": "toc"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/19c8aa1ed0195415/toc/np-227": {
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/19c8aa1ed0195415/toc/np-227",
